osu_versions.name: 1.2.4-5-osu-hidden
osu_versions.notes:
## What‚Äôs new in firmware version 1.2.4-5?

Firmware version 1.2.4-5 mainly brings support for Ethereum 2.0.
It also fixes a bug affecting a few users that upgraded to version [version 1.2.4-2](https://support.ledger.com/hc/en-us/articles/360014980580-Ledger-Nano-X-firmware-release-notes). Please find more information about this update in our [blog post](https://www.ledger.com/blog/ledger-is-ready-for-ethereum-2).

**Fixes**

- Apply the RDP lock directly during the update.
- Removed the MCU integrity check at each boot added in version [version 1.2.4-2](https://support.ledger.com/hc/en-us/articles/360014980580-Ledger-Nano-X-firmware-release-notes) to fix a rare bug where the device got stuck at ‚ÄúFollow device repair instructions‚Äù.

**Other changes**

- Addition of the possibility to perform a seed derivation according to the EIP 2333 key generation algorithm.

osu_versions.name: 1.2.4-5-osu
osu_versions.notes:
## What‚Äôs new in firmware version 1.2.4-5?

Firmware version 1.2.4-5 mainly brings support for Ethereum 2.0.
It also includes security enhancements, user experience improvements, additional cryptographic support and a few other changes. Please find more information about this update in our [blog post](https://www.ledger.com/blog/ledger-is-ready-for-ethereum-2).

**Security enhancements**

- Fixed a minor RDP lock vulnerability that could be used to make the device connect as a keyboard in the context of a supply chain attack, for example.

**Better user experience**

- Smooth update: no need to disconnect and reconnect the USB cable during firmware updates! Bootloader mode is now automatically launched to update the MCU firmware.
- Significantly reduced the delay when (un)installing multiple apps in the Manager.

**Other changes**

- Added cryptographic support for the Stark 256 and BLS12-381 curves.
- Addition of the possibility to perform a seed derivation according to the EIP 2333 key generation algorithm.
- Changes to the regulatory information, accessible through the settings or the boot menu.
- Fixed functionality to switch between library contexts.
